The goal for this project is to replace ALL rows with label 1 with a NEW
fraudulent_name, keeping the real name. Set up a system to, for each real name,
count the number of instances of label 1 in each file. After generating new
positive examples, replace 1:1 with the new generated data. So if real_name
google has 3 instances in validate, 3 new positive label-1 instances should go
to google.

Run Optuna trials to optimize:

1. Keep LEGIT score high, measured only on positive examples.
2. Keep Random Forest classifier ROC AUC toward 0.5 using a 90:10 split. There
   is no need to keep real names separate for text-distance metrics.

Run exactly 50 trials on all 9,999 validation examples. Keep negatives exactly
how they are and only replace positive rows. When replacing positive rows,
ensure that across all three files there are no duplicate fraudulent_names.

Optimize a range of possible change values and the randomization/skew of the
number of changes actually implemented. Replace the fixed character replacement
range with a length-aware percentage approach. Words should be grouped into
short, medium, and long categories. Short words should use a small fixed number
of replacements, while medium and long words should use a sampled percentage of
the word length. The sampled percentage should come from a configurable range
and can be skewed toward the lower end, middle, or higher end. Convert the
percentage into an integer replacement count by rounding, then cap the result
so it never exceeds the number of replaceable characters in the word. For
example, a 10-character word with a replacement range of 30% to 50% would
receive between 3 and 5 replacements, with values closer to 5 sampled more
frequently. Word length thresholds, percentage ranges, minimum replacement
count, maximum replacement cap, and sampling skew are configurable
hyperparameters.

Move old lookup-table work to LOOKUP_TABLE_DO_NOT_DELETE_FOR_NOW. Create
LOOKUP_TABLE_IN_USE with the approved OCR confusable swaps and the visually
identical/lookalike swaps. Use random adjacent swaps, random OCR-confusable
characters, random lookalike characters, etc. If a generated row does not
surpass LEGIT threshold 4, generate another attempt. If that does not pass,
generate another attempt. If all 3 do not pass, keep the row with the highest
LEGIT score. Do not keep trying infinitely. After generating the random final
change amounts, all three attempts should keep those values fixed.

If an Optuna trial has LEGIT score lower than 4, it should be treated as failing
the quality gate. Optuna should push LEGIT above 4 and try to push RF ROC AUC
below 0.75 or lower.

Make sure Optuna does not unfairly exclude parameters based on a single outlier
trial. Remember the order of operations and that swaps always go first. Only do
swaps if length is greater than or equal to 8. Swaps should not undo themselves
if multiple swaps are allowed. First designate which characters are being
replaced with what so later replacement steps do not overwrite earlier steps.
Similarly, do not undo steps such as a forward multicharacter substitution
followed by a reverse multicharacter substitution.

